body:
buildah v1.20.1
podman v3.1.2

I inherited a build procedure that uses buildah to construct an image starting FROM docker.io/centos:8, adds a bunch of things, and then does 

```buildah commit --squash --format docker <container> <tag>```

to create the final, intended-to-be-independent, image.  However, some record of the ancestry remains, and podman push mentions it in the config blob for a v2s2-format push, causing the repo server (quay.io) to reject the push, as it can't find the blob for "docker.io/centos:8", which of course it shouldn't need to.

podman inspect on the image shows a blank "Parent" field, and the only mention of the parent image is in a "History" section:

```
        "History": [
            {
                "created": "2021-05-17T20:49:55.561254531Z",
                "created_by": "/bin/sh",
                "comment": "FROM docker.io/library/centos:8"
            }
        ],
```
but somehow that's enough to allow push to form a reference to the image (captured from the http packet and formatted):
```
{
  "schemaVersion": 2,
  "mediaType": "application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json",
  "config": {
    "mediaType": "application/vnd.docker.container.image.v1+json",
    "size": 2646,
    "digest": "sha256:55815f5b8e9c3fce1e7855c73aa8adc9eb8111797659f6c6840857480d16a9de"
  },
  "layers": [
    {
      "mediaType": "application/vnd.docker.image.rootfs.diff.tar.gzip",
      "size": 224790428,
      "digest": "sha256:1cedb6d23e21ca650ff098273d219f9875a2baa08281d576a93d4bfc109a5412"
    }
  ]
}
```
@nalind helped me understand that that config blob is stored locally in /var/lib/containers/storage/overlay-images/55815f5b8e9c3fce1e7855c73aa8adc9eb8111797659f6c6840857480d16a9de/=c2hhMjU2OjU1ODE1ZjViOGU5YzNmY2UxZTc4NTVjNzNhYThhZGM5ZWI4MTExNzk3NjU5ZjZjNjg0MDg1NzQ4MGQxNmE5ZGU=, which contains:
```
  "architecture": "amd64",
  "os": "linux",
  "parent": "sha256:300e315adb2f96afe5f0b2780b87f28ae95231fe3bdd1e16b9ba606307728f55",
  "rootfs": {
    "type": "layers",
    "diff_ids": [
      "sha256:2b987497190f0eb7b5ddbaade7acad2f9f60df58c2c04fb7d01b9ad91fcc600a"
    ]
  },
  "history": [
    {
      "created": "2021-05-21T00:09:54.387702796Z",
      "created_by": "/bin/sh",
      "comment": "FROM docker.io/library/centos:8"
    }
  ]
```
so, like the 'inspect' output of the image, the "history" section, but unlike the inspect output, also an explicit "parent" reference to the intended-to-be-squashed-out image.
